Defendant Damian D Hullum in court with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
- Withheld sentence STAYED for 9 months Probation - 1 day if revoked.
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- DNA Surcharge waived.
- Conditions of  Probation: AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.   Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No drug paraphernalia. Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions. Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling. No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed. Mental Health/Psychological Evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
- Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service as a Condition of Probation
- 10 days jail Condition Time STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion.
